tournament.details:
## Welcome to the Battle Subway!

Departing from Nimbasa City in the Unova region, the Battle Subway offers only the best quality battles no matter where it stops! The Subway will travel all across the Smash Bros universe, and pick up some interesting contenders along the way. But first things first, we've got to start from somewhere. Where better to start than one of the first places we came to know in the game, the classic Battlefield? No one has any special treatment here, so everyone's got a chance to become the Subway Boss.

#### Schedule

Exact schedule TBA

#### Tournament Entry & Other Fees

###### Venue Fee: 
- $20 base fee
- $3 discount for preregister (before 11:59 PM on July 25th)
- $5 discount for setup (must have WiiU with Super Smash Bros for WiiU with all DLC and 1st party GameCube adapter, no monitor required)
- $2 discount for carpool (must have 4+ people to qualify, and all members of a carpool will receive the discount) OR out-of-state attendees (will be verified via region registered on smash.gg account)

###### Event Entry Fees:
- Singles: $10

Frequent visitor at Gamer's Heaven? If you sign up for at least a Silver level membership, you get free venue to not just Battle Subway, but also any other tournament or event hosted at Gamer's Heaven! Ask about memberships at the front desk of the store. And students, bring your ID to get a student discount when signing up.

The store also has lots of other items for sale. With the recent upgrade, they now have a full kitchen so you don't even have to leave the venue to get a meal! They also have other gaming related products, as well as store-branded merch. Make sure you bring along some extra money!

#### Commentary

Interested in commentating at Battle Subway? Fill out this form here: https://goo.gl/forms/83opDRy8m92WZimk1

#### Housing

Coming from far away and need a place to stay? Either contact the TO or join the Smash 4 Philly Facebook group (https://www.facebook.com/groups/Smash4Philly/) and we can try our best to help you out! There are also a few small hotels in the area, with larger hotels about 15-20 minutes away.

tournament.rules:
Reglas y Modalidad del PES 2019

— Cada jugador podrá elegir dos equipos ya sean selecciones o equipos
— Si los dos jugadores deciden jugar con el mismo equipo se lanzara la moneda y esta determinara quien elige equipo primero
— En un partido no se puede jugar con los mismo, ejemplo psg vs psg
— Todos los partidos son con velocidad 2x y de 10 min
— Todos los cambios se realizan al empezar el match y en el entretiempo
— Todos los partidos son con flecha al azar, verano y de día
— No se permite presionar pause ni home durante el match, sino pierde automáticamente 3-0
— Se pueden realizar cambios de jugador o quien ejecutara una falta en córners, saque de lateral, tiros libres, penales y saques de fondo
— El torneo sera por fase de grupo y luego eliminatorias
— El ganador se lleva 3 puntos y el empate 1
— Se permiten joystick externos
— No se permite ponerse de acuerdo para determinar un resultado, si se ve algún tipo de esta conducta el partido queda en empate

Reglas y Modalidad de SFV, KOF XIV Y DBFZ

Sistema de juego:
— Consola: PS4.
— Sistema de doble eliminación: se requiere perder dos enfrentamientos para quedar eliminado.
— Límite temporal: SFV 99 segundos, KOF XIV 60 segundos y DBZF 300 segundos 
— Al mejor de 3 rondas.
— Losers’ Final, Winners’ Final y Grand Final a 3 partidas al mejor de 5 rondas cada uno.

Reglas especiales:

— Se permitirá cambiar de personajes en cualquier ronda del torneo.
— Los jugadores disponen de un total de 3 minutos para seleccionar personajes y su respectiva configuración. Estos mismos son responsables de conocer cada una de las modificaciones a hacer previamente al torneo. La organización se reserva el derecho a descalificar a un jugador si supera el tiempo permitido.
— Se podrán configurar los controles de juego antes de comenzar la partida.
— El escenario será elegido de forma aleatoria, no obstante, si ambos jugadores se ponen de acuerdo, pueden luchar en un escenario de su elección.
— En caso de presionar home o option en medio de una batalla, se dará por perdida el round al causante del fallo.
— Solo el jugador perdedor podrá cambiar de personaje.
— Si uno de los jugadores se les sorprende insultando, agresión física, alguna situación anti reglamentaria, será expulsado del evento.

tournament.rules:
RULES FOR TEKKEN 7 TOURNAMENT

SET-UPS: All set-ups are endowed with Fat or Slim Ps4 and ZOWIE Monitors RL2460.

GAME MODE

All tournament matches will be played in VS mode which is set in the options as tournament mode.

BANNED CHARACTERS There will not be any banned characters. Should a new DLC character have any bugs or infinite combos, it will be banned. In case a Player wants to use a DLC character, he/she has to declare it when enrolling for the tournament so that organizers prepare the designated gaming stations and groups at their best.

GROUPS: The points will be scored according to Smash.gg score system. : All groups are played FT2, so the first Player winning 2 games, wins the match. Score is given as follows:

The first 4 Players qualified in each group get to the following tournament phase.

BRACKETS: This phase is Double Elimination. Each match is FT3, so the first Player winning 3 games, wins the match. In the Grand Final, the winner of Losers' bracket has to win two FT3 matches to win the tournament, whereas the winner of Winners' bracket has to win just one FT3 match to win the tournament.

CHARACTER LOCK: Only the Player losing a match can change character.

BUTTONS SETTING: Buttons must be set during the character selection by pressing ∆ button before choosing your character. You will not be able to change your button configuration after choosing your character since tournament mode disables options button.

STAGE LOCK Stage selection must be random at any time. When a Player loses a match, he/she is allowed to change stage, but his/her choice must be random anyway.

SIDE SELECTION Players may mutually agree who sits on the left and right side, corresponding to Player 1 and Player 2 respectively. If Players cannot agree, they will play Rock-Paper-Scissors to determine who picks their side.

HEADSET: All players are required to bring their own headset or head-phones since only the streaming gaming station is equipped with headset.

SMASH BROS ULTIMATE RULES: To be defined after official game launch.

BEHAVIOUR RULES: Offensive and violent behaviour is forbidden and results in disqualification from all ITL tournaments. Players are required to comply with the staff decision and tournament schedule. Players must be on time and play their match without wasting time or they will lose their match. *** ITALIANO

REGOLAMENTO DEL TORNEO DI TEKKEN 7

POSTAZIONI: tutte le postazioni di gioco ITL sono dotate di sistema Ps4 Fat o Slim e di Monitor ZOWIE RL2460.

MODALITA' DI GIOCO: tutti gli scontri dei tornei avvengono nella modalità VS, settata nelle opzioni come modalità Torneo.

PERSONAGGI BANNATI: non ci saranno personaggi bannati. L'unico caso di personaggio bannato è quello nel quale un nuovo personaggio rilasciato via DLC presenti dei bug o delle combo infinite.

IL PUNTEGGIO VERRA’ ASSEGNATO IN BASE AL REGOLAMENTO DI SMASH.GG

Le prime 4 persone di ogni girone passano alla fase successiva nel bracket a doppia eliminazione.

FASI A ELIMINAZIONE: La fase è a doppia eliminazione; le partite sono FT3 (vince chi per primo vince 3 partite);

FASI FINALI: il finalista proveniente dalla loser final deve battere 2 volte la persona proveniente dalla fase winner per aggiudicarsi il titolo di campione.

CHARACTER LOCK: dopo la prima sfida, il perdente può cambiare personaggio, mentre il vincente è costretto a riutilizzare lo stesso personaggio.

STAGE LOCK: lo stage iniziale viene deciso random; il perdente può decidere di cambiare stage dopo il primo incontro, ma la scelta del nuovo stage dev'essere effettuata nuovamente random.

CONFIGURAZIONE TASTI: i tasti vanno cambiati durante la selezione del personaggio. Non è possibile cambiarli una volta scelto lo stage, anche perchè la modalità torneo disabilita il tasto options.

SCELTA DEL LATO DI GIOCO: se entrambi i giocatori vogliono giocare da un lato di gioco, la scelta viene fatta tramite testa o croce o morra cinese. Il lato poi scelto è valido per tutti gli incontri

CONTROLLER E CUFFIE: ogni giocatore è tenuto a portare con sé il proprio pad o stick e a portarsi le proprie cuffie o i propri auricolari in quanto soltanto la postazione streaming è dotata di cuffie.

REGOLAMENTO DEL TORNEO DI SUPER SMASH BROS ULTIMATE (Da definire dopo il rilascio ufficiale del titolo).

REGOLE COMPORTAMENTALI: è vietato offendere il proprio avversario, pena sconfitta della partita; vietato avere comportamenti violenti, pena il BAN dal torneo; i giocatori sono tenuti a rispettare le decisioni degli organizzatori riguardo alle postazioni dove effettuare le sfide - se il giocatore si rifiuta di giocare dove gli è stato imposto dall'organizzatore o suo assistente, viene squalificato dal torneo. I giocatori sono inoltre tenuti a rispettare i tempi di gioco, e possono presentarsi una volta chiamati a giocare con un ritardo non superiore ai 10 minuti, pena la sconfitta a tavolino 2 0 in girone, 3 0 in bracket.

tournament.rules:
###MID-SET COACHING IS BANNED

General Gameplay:

- 3 Stock for Smash Ultimate, 4 stock for Melee
- 8 min stock timer for Ultimate, 8 Minute Stock Timer for Melee
- Items are set to "off" and "none"
- If the timer runs out, the victor is determined first by stock and then by percentage. If there is a tie, see the tiebreaker section to follow.
- Controller ports will be decided by players. If there is a conflict, players are welcome to settle the dispute with RPS
- You may switch controller ports on your counterpick only.
- BYOC (Bring your own controller). I recommend having a spare, just in case.
- Any controller malfunction mid match is on you. If you need to reset, your opponent will have to agree to a reset as doing so will require you to pause the match. (if pause is on).
- Stalling is banned. You know what this is, ask if you're unsure.
- If you freeze the game on an action initiated by your character, you lose the game. You are expected to know the boundaries of your character. (This rarely, if ever, happens.)
- Pause is recommended to be turned on for quick resets, but players can request it be turned off for the duration of their match.
- If a player pauses the match mid game (accidentally or intentionally), it is a stock loss to the player who pressed it (unless for valid interruption at T.O's discretion).
- A match ending in simultaneous death does not go to the initiator. If the result is sudden death from this, use the normal tiebreaking rules (to follow) to determine the winner. Otherwise use who the game declared the winner.
- Coaching mid-match is banned.
- You cannot re-select a stage you have won on as a counterpick.
- Any and all infinites (basically, where someone can control the opponent without them being able to do anything about it) must end at 300%, otherwise it becomes stalling. All infinites are entirely legal otherwise.
- Regular sets are 2 of 3. Winners', Losers' and Grand finals are 3 out of 5 for all Smash games.
- There are no bans in a 3 of 5 set.
- In the event of a game running to time, the winner is determined first by stocks, then % if the stocks are tied.
- 1 stage ban for Melee


Set Procedure:

1. Character selection
2. Stage strike (Players play RPS, winner determines who strikes first)
3. Play Game 1
4. Winning player announces banned stage(s) for the set.
5. Loser of previous match announces next match's stage
6. Winner of previous match chooses characters
7. Loser of previous match chooses characters
8. Play next game
9. Rinse and repeat 4-8 if set goes to a third game or fifth game.

Tie Breaking (Smash):


Note: Tiebreaking is only initiated if the game started a sudden death round upon completion. Otherwise, the game declared winner is the winner of the match.

1. Winner is determined by highest stock count then lowest percent.
2. 1 stock, 3 minute match is played as a tiebreaker match. The winner of this match wins the game. If there is a tie in this match, proceed to step 4. The LGL is modified for this match to 20.
3. A second 1 stock, no time limit match is played. If a simultaneous death is initiated (such as swallocide) in this match, the initiator loses the match. There is no tie for this match, it is play until you win.

Conduct Rules:

- Intentionally disrupting someone mid-match intentionally or accidentally is not acceptable. Please do your best to make sure you are not disrupting a match. This can result in a penalty at T.O.'s discretion.
- Don't lose anything you're bringing to the event please, we are not liable for lost/stolen etc.
- TTL Rule: You must register for the event on-time. Once the registration deadline is closed, no further entries will be permitted. Do not try to call me in advance to hold the bracket.
- Collusion of any kind (asking, intentionally throwing matches yourself, "agreeing to split", etc.) is subject to instant disqualification from all events and forfeiture of all prizes.

Additional Rules (Pokken)

Game Settings: LAN Mode, Skill=Off, 2/3 Rounds, 2/3 Games, Stadium Only
Loser of last match may change fighter Pokemon
Both players may change assist sets and cheer type between matches

tournament.gettingThere:
### How to get to Nørrebrohallen

#### Quick note on public transport

When you buy a public transport ticket in Copenhagen, whether it's a 2-zone or 3-zone ticket, you can use *any* type of public transport in the city, metro, bus or train within a time frame (usually 75-90 minutes).

#### From the airport (35 minutes approx.)

Head to the metro. Take the metro all the way to **Nørreport** (there is only one direction). At Nørreport, you can take bus 5C (direction Husum Torv) and get off at **Nørrebrohallen**. From there it's a one minute walk to the venue.

#### From Copenhagen Central Station (25 minutes approx.)

You have to take bus 5C (direction Husum Torv) which can be found outside the Bernstorffsgade exit of the station. Take bus 5C all the way to **Nørrebrohallen**. From there it's a one minute walk to the venue.

#### From the Nordhavn docks (30 minutes approx.)

Go to Nordhavn station. From there you can take bus 8A (direction Friheden st.), get off at **Nørrebros Runddel (Jagtvej)** and walk for 6 minutes on Nørrebrogade to the venue.

event.name: PES 2019 CUP
event.description:
PES 2019

— Cada jugador podrá elegir dos equipos ya sean selecciones o equipos
— Si los dos jugadores deciden jugar con el mismo equipo se lanzara la moneda y esta determinara quien elige equipo primero
— En un partido no se puede jugar con los mismo, ejemplo psg vs psg
— Todos los partidos son con velocidad 2x y de 10 min
— Todos los cambios se realizan al empezar el match y en el entretiempo
— Todos los partidos son con flecha al azar, verano y de día
— No se permite presionar pause ni home durante el match, sino pierde automáticamente 3-0
— Se pueden realizar cambios de jugador o quien ejecutara una falta en córners, saque de lateral, tiros libres, penales y saques de fondo
— El torneo sera por fase de grupo y luego eliminatorias
— El ganador se lleva 3 puntos y el empate 1
— Se permiten joystick externos
— No se permite ponerse de acuerdo para determinar un resultado, si se ve algún tipo de esta conducta el partido queda en empate

event.name: Dragon ball Fighterz
event.description:
DBFZ

Sistema de juego:
— Consola: PS4.
— Sistema de doble eliminación: se requiere perder dos enfrentamientos para quedar eliminado.
— Límite temporal: SFV 99 segundos, KOF XIV 60 segundos y DBZF 300 segundos 
— Al mejor de 3 rondas.
— Losers’ Final, Winners’ Final y Grand Final a 3 partidas al mejor de 5 rondas cada uno.

Reglas especiales:

— Se permitirá cambiar de personajes en cualquier ronda del torneo.
— Los jugadores disponen de un total de 3 minutos para seleccionar personajes y su respectiva configuración. Estos mismos son responsables de conocer cada una de las modificaciones a hacer previamente al torneo. La organización se reserva el derecho a descalificar a un jugador si supera el tiempo permitido.
— Se podrán configurar los controles de juego antes de comenzar la partida.
— El escenario será elegido de forma aleatoria, no obstante, si ambos jugadores se ponen de acuerdo, pueden luchar en un escenario de su elección.
— En caso de presionar home o option en medio de una batalla, se dará por perdida el round al causante del fallo.
— Solo el jugador perdedor podrá cambiar de personaje.
— Si uno de los jugadores se les sorprende insultando, agresión física, alguna situación anti reglamentaria, será expulsado del evento.
